 Either in 945 or 957, the ruling regent, [[Olga of Kiev]], visited [[Constantinople]] with a certain priest, Gregory. Her reception at the imperial court is described in ''[[De Ceremoniis]]''. According to legends, [[Byzantine Emperor]] [[Constantine VII]] fell in love with Olga; however, she found a way to refuse him by tricking him into becoming her [[godparent|godfather]]. When she was baptized, she said it was inappropriate for a godfather to marry his [[goddaughter]].{{citation needed|date=January 2023}}

